data-triple-N3.o: "In mathematics, twovariablesareproportional ifa change in one is always accompanied by a change in the other, and if the changes are always related by use of a constant. The constant is called the coefficient of proportionality or proportionality constant. Alternatively, we can say that one of the variables is proportional to the other. If one variable is always theproduct oftheother and aconstant, the two are said to be directly proportional."@en
